http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Fresh-notice-to-Jayarajan-in-Manoj-murder-case/article13985733.ece

The Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI) team investigating the murder of Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh (RSS) functionary E. Manoj served a notice on Communist Party of India (Marxist) district secretary P. Jayarajan to appear before the investigating officers at Thalassery on Wednesday. According to CPI(M) sources, Mr. Jayarajan, however, despatched a petition seeking exemption from appearing on Wednesday citing personal inconveniences.Mr. Jayarajan was served notice by the CBI on January 5. He was asked to appear before the investigating officers at the Government Rest House at Thalassery at 11 a.m. on Wednesday for questioning in connection with the murder case.The party sources said that Mr. Jayarajan sent the exemption petition through a messenger at 10 a.m. He assured the CBI team that he would appear before it on a convenient date next week. Manoj had been hacked to death at Kathirur, near Panur, by alleged CPI(M) workers on September 1, 2014. Mr. Jayarajan is one of the accused in the case.Following an earlier notice by the CBI, Mr. Jayarajan had appeared before the CBI team on June 2 last year.The charge sheet filed by the CBI in the trial court listed 19 accused and identified political vengeance as the prime motive of the crime. The victim was an accused in the case of attack on Mr. Jayarajan in 1999.The fresh notice served by the CBI triggered speculation about possible outcomes of the ongoing investigation. On the occasion of the earlier notice, there had been speculation in political circles that Mr. Jayarajan was facing arrest in the case.